<body>
  
  
  <bookmark branch="index" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3146121"><bookmark_value>importing; presentations with HTML</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>presentations; importing HTML</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>HTML; importing into presentations</bookmark_value></bookmark><paragraph id="hd_id3146121" role="heading" level="1" oldref="1" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="html_import"><link href="text/simpress/guide/html_import.xhp" name="Importing HTML Pages Into Presentations ">Importing HTML Pages Into Presentations </link></variable></paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3150750" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="2">You can import any text file, including text in HTML documents, into a slide.</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="3" id="hd_id3155443" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="11">To insert text from a file into a slide:</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3146313" l10n="U" oldref="4">In the slide where you want to insert the text, choose <emph>Insert - File</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3150207" l10n="U" oldref="5">Select &quot;Text&quot; or &quot;HTML Document&quot; as the <emph>File type</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3148610" l10n="U" oldref="12">Locate the file containing the text that you want to add, and then click <emph>Insert</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3153915" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="6">If the text file contains more text than can be inserted into a single slide, you can divide the text over several slides.</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3149126" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="7">Double-click in the inserted text to enter edit mode.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3143228" l10n="U" oldref="8">Select all of the text that lies below the visible slide area and press <switchinline select="sys"> <caseinline select="MAC">Command</caseinline> <defaultinline>Ctrl</defaultinline> </switchinline>+X.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="9" role="listitem" id="par_id3153811" l10n="U">Choose <emph>Insert â€“ Slide</emph>, and then press <switchinline select="sys"> <caseinline select="MAC">Command</caseinline> <defaultinline>Ctrl</defaultinline> </switchinline>+V.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147297" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="10">Repeat steps 1  to 3 until all of the text is on slides.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
